The paper deals with a graph theory problem and proposes an algorithmic approach to solve it. The problem involves finding a subgraph with certain properties, which is a common theme in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithmic approach involves computing representative families of co-graphic matroids, which is a technique used in graph theory (cs.DS) and combinatorial optimization (cs.CC). Finally, the paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and the proposed algorithm, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.GT).
